latestPosts.caption:
Last spam post, I promise! Since some of you were eager to know the details about my Nikkah, here it is! 

I chose to wear a stunning green gharara from @karishmatheweddingmall , inspired by the beautiful Iranian tradition where brides wear green on their nikkah as a symbol of paradise, purity, and prosperity. To make it even more special, I wore my mom’s 31 year old wedding jadavi and Karan phool jewelry, which added a truly priceless, sentimental touch to my overall look, it felt like I had a piece of her love and blessings with me! My Sofreh Aghd, beautifully set up by my lovely sister, was a thoughtful representation of our new life together, bringing together elements that symbolize health, happiness, and prosperity for our marriage. 🥰

A huge shoutout to my incredible makeup artist @nooraanabila who understood my vision perfectly and created a subtle, natural look that I adore! My hairstylist @hairbyfirdouse did a fabulous job with my braid hairstyle, adding the perfect touch to my overall look! The beautiful henna design, crafted by @mehendi_wings , added an extra layer of elegance to my special day! And of course, thanks to @mizaankhanphotography for capturing everything so beautifully! 

I’m so grateful to have shared this special day with all of you! 🥹✨
